cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes the propagation of viral memes in Twitter messages and the communication network connecting countries and states of the world.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper may involve the development of algorithms or software tools for analyzing the propagation of viral memes.
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper applies computational methods to study social phenomena such as the spread of viral memes.
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper may discuss the security and privacy implications of viral memes spreading through online communication networks.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a less likely category but possible as the paper may involve the analysis of multimedia content such as videos and images in the context of viral memes.
